Eskom announced on Friday afternoon that loadshedding will be reduced from stage 2 to stage 1 from 10pm tonight. The power utility said this was due to lower weekend demand. Stage 1 is expected to last until 5am on Monday. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.